solution.p:
Define pigeonholes to be the sets 
 \{1,4\}, \{ 2,5\}, \{3,6\}, \{7, 10\}, \{8, 11\}, \{9, 12\}
and pigeons to be the integers selected from \{1,2,\ldots,12\};
assign each integer selected to the bin that contains that number.

