solution.p:
For the pairwise intersections |A_i \cap A_j| the only difference is that we are fixing two pairs to begin, and then grouping the remaining 2n-4 animals into pairs.
This means that for any i \ne j we have

	|A_i \cap A_j| \amp = \binom{2n-4}{2}\binom{2n-6}{2}\cdots\binom{4}{2}\binom{2}{2}\dfrac{1}{(n-1)!}
	\amp = \dfrac{(2n-4)!}{2!\ (2n-6)!}\cdot\dfrac{(2n-6)!}{2!\ (2n-8)!}\cdots\dfrac{4!}{2!\ 2!}\cdot \dfrac{2!}{2! \ 0!} \cdot \dfrac{1}{(n-1)!}
	\amp = \dfrac{(2n-4)!}{(2!)^{n-2}\ (n-2)!}
